[CENTER][SIZE=6][B]EssentialsMiniReload[/B][/SIZE]
[SIZE=4]A lightweight, modular essentials plugin for modern Minecraft servers[/SIZE]

[B]Homes | Warps | Spawn | Economy | Kits | Moderation | Private Messages | Mail | Nicknames | Backpacks | Utility Stations | Recipes[/B]
[/CENTER]

[SIZE=5][B]Overview[/B][/SIZE]

EssentialsMiniReload is a modern essentials plugin for Spigot, Paper, and Purpur servers. It brings together the most common server tools in one lightweight plugin, so you do not need a large stack of separate plugins for everyday commands.

The plugin includes homes, warps, spawn management, economy commands, kits, moderation tools, private messages, mail, nicknames, backpacks, portable utility stations, recipe helpers, inventory utilities, world controls, and more.

It is designed for Minecraft [B]1.20.6 and higher[/B] and runs on Java 17.

Need support for older Minecraft versions? Use the original EssentialsMini plugin:
[URL]https://www.spigotmc.org/resources/essentialsmini.82775/[/URL]

[SIZE=5][B]Features[/B][/SIZE]

[LIST]
[*][B]Spawn System[/B] - Set and teleport to the server spawn.
[*][B]Homes[/B] - Set, delete, and teleport to homes.
[*][B]Home GUI[/B] - Open a GUI to manage and select homes.
[*][B]Warps[/B] - Create, delete, list, and teleport to warps.
[*][B]Teleport Requests[/B] - TPA, TPAHere, accept, deny, and teleport toggles.
[*][B]Back Command[/B] - Return to your last death or previous location.
[*][B]Economy[/B] - Balance, pay, balance top, eco admin commands, and bank features.
[*][B]Filesystem Banks[/B] - Bank data works with the default YAML economy storage in [CODE]plugins/EssentialsMini/money/eco.yml[/CODE].
[*][B]Vault Support[/B] - Economy integration through Vault.
[*][B]Kits[/B] - Create kits, use permission-based kits, and browse available kits in a GUI.
[*][B]Inventory Tools[/B] - Invsee, ender chest, backpack, trash, repair, item commands, and portable utility stations.
[*][B]Portable Utility Stations[/B] - Open crafting, anvil, grindstone, smithing table, cartography table, loom, and stonecutter menus anywhere.
[*][B]Recipe Helpers[/B] - Show item recipes and retrieve ingredients from crafted items.
[*][B]Moderation[/B] - Mute, temp mute, ban, temp ban, unban, global mute, maintenance mode, and clear chat.
[*][B]Private Messaging[/B] - Message, reply, spy, and message toggle commands.
[*][B]Mail System[/B] - Send and manage player mail.
[*][B]Nicknames[/B] - Set player nicknames, apply skins through ProtocolLib, reset nicknames, and view nickname lists.
[*][B]Command Help GUI[/B] - Use [CODE]/emhelp[/CODE] to browse every EssentialsMiniReload command in a paged GUI with hover lore for description, usage, aliases, and permission.
[*][B]Player Utilities[/B] - Fly, god mode, heal, feed, speed, AFK, time played, online/offline player lists.
[*][B]World Controls[/B] - Day, night, sun, rain, thunder, player time, player weather, lightning, and firework commands.
[*][B]Geyser and Floodgate Support[/B] - Optional Bedrock player support where Geyser/Floodgate are available.
[*][B]Custom Message Locales[/B] - Add server-owned [CODE]messages_<locale>.yml[/CODE] files, enable them in config, and manage them with [CODE]/essentialsmini messages[/CODE].
[*][B]Deep Customization[/B] - Toggle and customize feature prefixes, chat/actionbar/title/sound notifications, disabled-command messages, and GUI titles/items.
[*][B]Multiple Storage Options[/B] - YAML, SQLite, MySQL, and MongoDB support depending on the feature.
[/LIST]

[SIZE=5][B]Latest 1.1.3 Highlights[/B][/SIZE]

[LIST]
[*]Create and enable custom [CODE]messages_<locale>.yml[/CODE] files without editing the plugin jar.
[*]Manage custom message files with [CODE]/essentialsmini messages list[/CODE], [CODE]add[/CODE], [CODE]remove[/CODE], and [CODE]create[/CODE].
[*]Customize feature prefixes, notification delivery, disabled-command messages, and GUI titles/items from [CODE]config.yml[/CODE].
[*]Use the new [CODE]/kits[/CODE] selector GUI when no kit name is supplied.
[*]Safely customize backpack and warp GUI titles/items without breaking inventory saving or warp clicks.
[/LIST]

[B]Recent bug fixes[/B]

[LIST]
[*]Filesystem-backed banks now work consistently for create, remove, balance, deposit, withdraw, transfer, member management, list, and info commands.
[*]Filesystem banks are no longer removed by stale player-balance saves after bank deposits or balance updates.
[*]Bank names are validated for safe YAML storage and may contain letters, numbers, underscores, and hyphens.
[*]Filesystem bank lookup is case-insensitive while preserving the original bank display name.
[*]Filesystem bank owner/member checks now support legacy player-name entries and UUID-backed ownership data.
[*][CODE]/sleep[/CODE] now restores temporary bed blocks safely per player and handles invalid [CODE]BedColor[/CODE] values cleanly.
[*]Economy signs can recover the Vault economy provider after startup if it was not ready during listener construction.
[*]Stored warp locations are collected from the correct [CODE]warps.<name>[/CODE] paths.
[*]Saved location loading now handles missing worlds, malformed serialized locations, and null locations more safely.
[*]GUI helper code now handles missing inventories and empty-slot lookups more safely.
[*]Backpack contents now save correctly even when the backpack GUI title is customized.
[*]Warp GUI clicks no longer depend on parsing the displayed item name, so custom warp item names are safe.
[*]Custom message files are detected, normalized, and reported more clearly when they still need to be enabled.
[*]Disabled-command responses for [CODE]/help[/CODE], [CODE]/?[/CODE], [CODE]/me[/CODE], and plugin-list commands can now use configured messages.
[/LIST]

[SIZE=5][B]Requirements[/B][/SIZE]

[LIST]
[*]Minecraft server running Spigot, Paper, or Purpur
[*]Minecraft version: [B]1.20.6 or higher[/B]
[*]Java: [B]17 or higher[/B]
[/LIST]

[SIZE=5][B]Optional Dependencies[/B][/SIZE]

[LIST]
[*][B]Vault[/B] - Required for economy integration.
[*][B]LuckPerms[/B] - Recommended for permission management.
[*][B]ProtocolLib[/B] - Used for extended packet-based features such as live skin refreshes.
[*][B]Geyser-Spigot[/B] - Optional support for Bedrock players.
[*][B]floodgate[/B] - Optional support for Bedrock account checks with Geyser setups.
[/LIST]

[SIZE=5][B]Installation[/B][/SIZE]

[LIST=1]
[*]Download the plugin jar.
[*]Place the jar inside your server's [CODE]plugins[/CODE] folder.
[*]Start or restart your server.
[*]Edit the generated configuration files in [CODE]plugins/EssentialsMini/[/CODE].
[*]Restart the server again after configuring.
[/LIST]

