[SIZE=5][B]Configuration[/B][/SIZE]

The plugin generates configuration and data files automatically after the first server start.

Common files include:

[LIST]
[*][CODE]config.yml[/CODE]
[*]Language/message files such as [CODE]messages_en-EN.yml[/CODE]
[*]Custom language/message files such as [CODE]messages_nl-NL.yml[/CODE]
[*][CODE]locations.yml[/CODE]
[*][CODE]kits.yml[/CODE]
[*][CODE]mail.yml[/CODE]
[*][CODE]tempMutes.yml[/CODE]
[*][CODE]nicks.yml[/CODE]
[/LIST]

You can customize messages, storage options, economy settings, moderation behavior, and many other plugin features.

Existing [CODE]config.yml[/CODE] files are updated with missing default options and bundled comments on startup or [CODE]/essentialsmini reload[/CODE] without overwriting configured values.

[B]Custom message locales[/B]

Add custom message files to [CODE]plugins/EssentialsMini/[/CODE] using the [CODE]messages_<locale>.yml[/CODE] naming format, for example [CODE]messages_nl-NL.yml[/CODE].

If a custom file exists but is not enabled, EssentialsMiniReload logs a prompt explaining how to add it. You can enable it with [CODE]/essentialsmini messages add <locale>[/CODE] or by adding the locale to [CODE]messages.customLocales[/CODE] in [CODE]config.yml[/CODE].

Use [CODE]/essentialsmini messages create <locale>[/CODE] to copy the English messages into a new custom locale file and enable it immediately. Use [CODE]/essentialsmini messages list[/CODE] to view loaded locales, enabled custom locales, and custom files that still need to be added.

[CODE]messages:
  customLocales:
    - nl-NL
  promptForCustomLocales: true[/CODE]

[B]Customization[/B]

The [CODE]customization[/CODE] section in [CODE]config.yml[/CODE] lets server owners toggle and customize common visible behavior:

[LIST]
[*][CODE]customization.prefixes[/CODE] - Feature-specific prefixes for economy, moderation, mail, teleport, help, kits, backpack, trash, and utility stations.
[*][CODE]customization.notifications[/CODE] - Chat, actionbar, title, and sound delivery for teleport requests, teleport completion, teleport delay, mail received, and money received.
[*][CODE]customization.disabledCommands[/CODE] - A default disabled-command message plus per-command overrides such as [CODE]help[/CODE], [CODE]me[/CODE], and [CODE]plugins[/CODE].
[*][CODE]customization.guis[/CODE] - Titles and item materials/names/lore for home, warp, kit selector, trash, backpack, and utility station interfaces.
[/LIST]

Feature prefixes are disabled by default to preserve existing behavior. Enable them when you want per-feature branding:

[CODE]customization:
  prefixes:
    enabled: true
    features:
      economy:
        enabled: true
        value: '&6[&eEconomy&6] &f'[/CODE]

Notifications can be sent through chat, actionbar, title, and sound channels. Available notification groups include [CODE]teleportRequestReceived[/CODE], [CODE]teleportRequestSent[/CODE], [CODE]teleportCompleted[/CODE], [CODE]teleportDelay[/CODE], [CODE]mailReceived[/CODE], and [CODE]moneyReceived[/CODE].

Useful notification placeholders include [CODE]%Player%[/CODE], [CODE]%Target%[/CODE], [CODE]%Time%[/CODE], [CODE]%Sender%[/CODE], and [CODE]%Money%[/CODE].

[CODE]customization:
  notifications:
    moneyReceived:
      enabled: true
      chat:
        enabled: true
        message: '&aYou received &6%Money% &afrom &6%Player%&a.'
      actionbar:
        enabled: true
        message: '&a+%Money% from &6%Player%'[/CODE]

Disabled-command messages can be configured globally or per command. EssentialsMiniReload uses [CODE]/emhelp[/CODE] and [CODE]/essentialshelp[/CODE] for plugin help because Bukkit/Spigot owns [CODE]/help[/CODE].

[CODE]customization:
  disabledCommands:
    usePerCommandMessages: true
    defaultMessage: '&cYou are not allowed to use &6%Command%&c.'
    commands:
      help: '&cUse &6/emhelp &cfor EssentialsMiniReload help.'
      plugins: '&cPlugins are hidden on this server.'[/CODE]

GUI customization supports titles, item materials, names, and lore for supported interfaces. Warp clicks and backpack saving are handled internally, so custom item names and titles are safe to use.

For [B]/nick <nickname> <skin>[/B] troubleshooting, enable [CODE]skinDebug: true[/CODE] in [CODE]config.yml[/CODE], reload or restart the server, then check the console for [CODE][SkinDebug][/CODE] lines.

Skin refresh supports Spigot, Paper, and Purpur by trying Paper/Purpur profile APIs first and falling back to ProtocolLib/NMS profile updates on Spigot-style servers.

[SIZE=5][B]Storage Support[/B][/SIZE]

EssentialsMiniReload supports different storage systems depending on your setup:

[LIST]
[*]YAML files
[*]SQLite
[*]MySQL
[*]MongoDB
[/LIST]

